The paper discusses personalized recommender systems, which are commonly studied in the information retrieval (cs.IR) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The use of collaborative tags to improve recommendations also suggests a focus on social networks and social media (cs.SOC). Additionally, the evaluation of the algorithm on three different data sets suggests a potential focus on databases (cs.DB). Finally, the use of graph-based algorithms for recommendation suggests a potential focus on network science and complex systems (cs.SI).
